For example, a patient with ovarian cancer lost cancer cells within 18 months after being treated with a vaccine that teaches the immune system to recognize malignant cells.
The method involves the isolation of resistant cells from the patient and their modification in the laboratory so that they are able to ‘see’ the HER2 proteins that are typical of many cancers.
